The paper discusses the use of a domain-specific design language and compiler for developing robotics systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for correctness and runtime support, which are relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits and problems of using the framework, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
